  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Providing health assistance to address the immediate needs of displaced populations affected by the Nagorno-Karabakh conflict in Armenia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to respond to health needs through primary health care services and Mental Health and Psychosocial Support (MHPSS) activities in the displacement sites. This IOM project provides 1) health teams composed of a physician, pediatrician, nurse, therapist, sonographer and a psychologist, and trains them on Psychological First Aid (PFA) to conduct primary health care consultations with adults and children and 2) focused MHPSS services to those in need. The project provides assistance to 9,400 people, including 4,300 women, 1,100 men, 4,000 children, and 840 people with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
